|Inferences={{Inference
|Inference.Description=The motion impediment negatively affects the mover's motion (e.g. slows or stops motion and/or increases energy needed for mover to move).
|Inference.Type=causal
}}{{Inference
|Inference.Description=Causing a motion impediment to be present (indirectly) causes a negative effect on mover's motion.
|Inference.Type=causal
}}{{Inference
|Inference.Description=Removing a motion impediment removes the negative effect on mover's motion.
|Inference.Type=causal
}}{{Inference
|Inference.Description=The presence of an impediment may prevent mover from reaching goal.
